14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 858-732, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 858-732. A. All persons listed in paragraph 2 of
18 subsection A of Section 858-702 of this title must conduct all real
19 property valuations and any real property valuation-related activity
20 in conformance with the following:
21 1. An appraiser must perform ethically and competently and not
22 engage in conduct that is unlawful, unethical or improper. An
23 appraiser who could reasonably be perceived to act as a
24 disinterested third party in rendering an unbiased real property
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1081 Page 1

1 valu ation must perform assignments with impartiality, objectivity
2 and independence and without accommodation of personal interests;
3 2. The acceptance of compensation that is contingent upon the
4 reporting of a predetermined value or a direction in value that
5 favors the cause of the client, the amount of the value estimate,
6 the attainment of a stipulated result or the occurrence of a
7 subsequent event is unethical;
8 3. The payment of undisclosed fees, commissions or things of
9 value in connection with the procurement of real property valuation
10 assignments is unethical;
11 4. When providing residential appraisal services, an invoice
12 for service exhibiting compensation to the appraiser must be
13 included as the first page in all assignments;
14 5. Advertising for or soliciting appraisal assignments in a
15 manner which is false, misleading or exaggerated is unethical;
16 5. 6. An appraiser must protect the confidential nature of the
17 appraiser-client relationship; and
18 6. 7. Using or attempting to use the seal, certificate, or
19 license of another as their own; falsely impersonating any duly
20 licensed appraiser; using or attempting to use an inactive, expired,
21 suspended, or revoked license; or aiding or abetting any of the
22 foregoing is unethical.
23 B. Although this code of ethics is based upon the ethics
24 provisions of the Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal
