1 Prac tice, it is not the intent of the Legislature to incorporate the
2 standards set forth in the Uniform Standards of Professional
3 Appraisal Practice.
4 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 858-818, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 858-818. A. An AMC registered under the Oklahoma
7 Appraisal Management Company Regulation Act shall be required to
8 have a system in place to disclose to its client the fees paid for
9 appraisal management services and the fees paid to the appraiser for
10 the completion for an appraisal assignment.
11 B. An AMC registered under the Oklahoma Appraisal Management
12 Company Regulation Act that applies for registration in this state
13 shall accept and shall not prohibit an appraiser that is part of an
14 appraiser panel of the AMC from including an invoice as an
15 attachment to the appraisal recording the fee that the appraiser was
16 paid by the AMC for the performance of the appraisal within the
17 communication of the appraisal that is submitted by the appraiser to
18 the AMC. Any demand by an AMC or its employees to an appraiser to
19 remove an invoice, or if an AMC or its employees remove an attached
20 invoice to the appraisal recording fee, showing the appraiser was
21 paid by the AMC for performance of the appraisal are in violation of
22 this act and shall be subject to penalties under Section 858-827 of
23 this title.
24 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
